un)","Al-Kafirun","Surah Al-Kafirun"],"ayahNumber":6210,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"si"},{"name":"109:4","price":"තවද නුඹලා නැමදූ දෑ මම නමදින්නෙක් නො වූයෙමි.","arabic":"وَلَآ أَنَا۠ عَابِدٞ مَّا عَبَدتُّمۡ","category":["109 (Al-Kafirun)","Al-Kafirun","Surah Al-Kafirun"],"ayahNumber":6211,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"si"},{"name":"109:5","price":"තවද මා නමදින දෑ නුඹලා ද නමදින්නෝ නො වූහ.","arabic":"وَلَآ أَنتُمۡ عَٰبِدُونَ مَآ أَعۡبُدُ","category":["109 (Al-Kafirun)","Al-Kafirun","Surah Al-Kafirun"],"ayahNumber":6212,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"si"},{"name":"109:6","price":"නුඹලාට නුඹලාගේ දහම ය. මට මාගේ දහම ය.","arabic":"لَكُمۡ دِينُكُمۡ وَلِيَ دِينِ","category":["109 (Al-Kafirun)","Al-Kafirun","Surah Al-Kafirun"],"ayahNumber":6213,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"si"}],"dua":{"id":2,"name":"Four Quls (Al-Arba' Qul)","arabicName":"الأربع قل","reference":"112:1-4, 113:1-5, 114:1-6, 109:1-6","verseTitle":"The Four Declarations of Divine Oneness and Protection","significanceReason":"Considered a complete spiritual protection and declaration of divine unity, represent spiritual protection, affirmation of divine oneness, rejection of polytheism, and seeking refuge from all forms of harm, recited for spiritual defense, mental peace, and as a comprehensive protection against negative energies, jealousy, and spiritual afflictions."}}